latestIgtvVideos.title: Nail oil ✨ by @arainabyarshneet 💛
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Gold ! ✨
Nail oil 💛 by @arainabyarshneet !
I am breaking down the review in parts (keeping it as to the point as possible)
.
✨Order experience from Araina✨
Incredible 💛 She has been extremely cooperative and patient, because I annoyed her a lot, and she made sure that my order was perfectly completed.
✨ About the oil ✨
A blend of growth stimulating, healing and strengthening oils like vit e (tocopherol), jojoba oil, jamaican black castor oil, borage seed oil and argan oil, this oil blend helps keep your nails and cuticles nourished and flexible which in turn prevents breakage. (TAKEN FROM THE WEBSITE)
It retails for 
650/- for 30ml (dropper)
595/- for 12ml (with nail polish bottle)

✨How to use✨
See in the video.
Time : Whenever I feel like. (Certainly after washing)
Mostly around the cuticles and nails and knuckles, and sometimes whole hand till the wrist.
✨My experience ✨
💛 It has a mild and fresh smell!
💛 Quick absorbent, doesn't feel greasy or heavy at all.
💛 You can see how little is needed.
💛 It has certainly made my nails healthier, the conditions went down hill during the end of May, and you can seethe change till today! 
💛 My nails are more flexible and stronger without any doubt.
💛 The clear appearance has almost gone, it'll take time to go completely.
.
✨ Do I recommend? ✨
💯 ! If you want strong healthy nails, YES you do neeed this.
Even though it might seem expensive, but it is very economical. You need very little, it'll last you a LONG TIME, and the results are AMAZING! They serve the best quality! You'll realise that they are not just affordable rather low priced! 
.
.
if you have any queries, feel free to drop a comment !

latestPosts.caption:
My favourite reds ❤️
Christmas is all about red!! ✨
So here are my favourites that YOU MUST MUST TRY!

1. Struck by Cupid @nykaacosmetics 
It's a metallic red with pink undertones, it looks very soft, yet bright.
2. Antares by @debellecosmetix 
It's a metallic red too but it has pink flakes running through, and it's a bit darker than others.
3. Metallic Red by @reneeofficial 
It's a basic metallic red, not as thick as Nykaa's, and has warmer undertones.
4. Red glitter by @missnailsforyou 
It's a red jelly base with red sparkly glitters that shine through beautifully.
5. Jhil Mil by @lovechildbymasaba 
It's a red jelly base filled with rose gold, and red flakies, and red shimmer. It's one of a kind!

Let me know your favourite among these and if there's anything else you'd like to add to this list!
